miscConds.notes: Defendant must pay all outstanding fees and court obligations including costs of probation during the term of probation. If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant and in favor of restitution victims and governmental entities for the balance due.  Collections may include income assignment.

No alcohol or controlled substances except by prescription. Random UA's are authorized. Must participate and complete any counseling deemed appropriate by agent. Defendant must obtain and maintain full time verifiable employment. Defendant has already provided a DNA specimen, as required by law, however he is responsible for the surcharge. Defendant must comply with any family court orders.  Defendant must obey all rules and regulations while on probation.
